doc_summary_long: Some Orange County residents were stunned Thursday, Sept. 22, when television programming was suddenly interrupted for about a minute with an ominous message predicting the end of the world. Stacy Laflamme of Lake Forest said she was watching the Home and Gardens Television network via Cox Communication about 11:05 a.m. when suddenly an emergency alert flashed across her screen followed by a voice that spoke about the end of times. 'Realize this, extremely violent times will come,' a man's voice boomed, according to a video of the alert.
doc_summary_short: Some Orange County residents were stunned Thursday, Sept. 22, when television programming was suddenly interrupted for about a minute with an ominous message predicting the end of the world.
doc_title: End-of-world prediction interrupts TV broadcasts in Orange County
